@Kamei JohnWilson sir, you are definitely not wrong. I completely understand the necessity of having a larger agglomeration like pan naga in Manipur context. Its uniquely diverse. Iam simply trying to understand the Nation definition criteria here. When we say KuKi-Chin-Mizo its just like Ze-Liang- Rong.   Zemei- Liangmei- Rongmei all distributed in Manipur, Assam, Nagaland, etc. Diverse but same root of a large tree in terms of language and intrinsic culture. Just that the size is bigger in case of KuKi-Chin-Mizo. Same thing for the Meitei Salai7. Same thing for Britain/UK - Scottish, Irish, english. Same for Israel-12tribes/sons but all speak Hebrew/Aramaic bonded by1 Abraham and holy book Torah. Maybe slightly different cultures, different accents but 1 rooted nation and language. We can't ignore the Language criteria at all when we try to define a nation. At least till the present era. Ukhrul and Mao are just neighbors for generations but they are very uniquely different in language and culture . Eg: the manipur naga festival Lui-Ngai-Ni: lui- tangkhul, Ngai-rongmei, Ni- mao. The spirit of uniting tribes can be apllauded but the tribe historical fabrication and alterations just to reach the top of power hierarchy or eliminate another tribe like Kuki by Ukhrul is unfortunate.
